VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT (\b.disable\(\s*['"]csrf['"]\s*\))
WHEN EXPR MISSING:CsrfTokenRepository|csrfTokenRequestAttributeName|SameSite && PRESENT:csrf\(\)\.disable\(\)|csrf\.disable\(\)|CsrfConfigurer
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects disabled CSRF (Cross-Site Request Forgery) protection in Java code.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for Disabled CSRF Protection.
